-- Sumitomo to Invest $322 Million in Brazilian Plant, Estado Says
-- B y   T e l m a   M a r o t t o
-- 2012-01-28T14:30:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-28/sumitomo-to-invest-322-million-in-brazilian-plant-estado-says.html
Sumitomo Rubber Industries Ltd., a
Japanese maker of automobile and motorcycle tires, plans to
invest 560 million reais ($322 million) in a factory in the
Brazilian southern state of Parana, O Estado de S. Paulo
reported.  The plant will be ready in 2013 and will produce as many as
15,000 tires per day, the newspaper said, citing company
executives Ikuji Ikeda and Ippei Oda, and Parana Governor Beto
Richa. The facility will generate 1,500 jobs by 2017, Estado
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Telma Marotto in  Sao Paulo  at 
 tmarotto1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Helder Marinho at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net . 